The results of the scheme in which the ring geometry is determined without taking radial motions into account are shown on the right side. During the initial tilted ring fit the position angle is fitted to a value that compensates for the radial motion (upper right panel). In the subsequent Fourier decomposition only a small fraction of the actual radial velocity signal is recovered. The Fourier decomposition is not able to find the correct inflow because it is restricted to the wrong ring geometry.}
\label{Mock2403}
