	\includegraphics[width=\widthsingle]{fig6_NGC2403_Hermite}
	\caption{A comparison of the radial inflow pattern derived from a standard THINGS first moment map and from a velocity map computed by fitting Hermite functions to the H\,{\sc i} spectra. The Hermite map gives slightly different results than the moment map: From 450'' to 550'' the inflow rate is higher, from 600'' to 800'' lower. However, the overall distribution of radial velocities is quite comparable. We note that the moment map extends to further radii, which is important for the analysis presented here. 
	} 
